    <h4>
        Leadership Development</h4>
    <p>
        Beginning in September RPC will be conducting training in leadership that focuses
        on character, theology and skills. The training will involve directed self-study
        and regular group meetings over the next six months, skipping the month of December.
        The first three months are open to all those interested, both men and women. The
        last two months will be open to men preparing for specific office, who have successfully
        completed the general training. Participants will be expected to complete all readings
        and assignments in preparation for a group meeting every other week. It breaks down
        this way.</p>
    <h3>
        General Leadership Development</h3>
    <ul type="disc">
        <li>Self-study will focus on Reformed theology, Presbyterian church polity and history,
            RPC distinctives, biblical patterns and principles of leadership, and church renewal</li>
        <li>Meeting schedule: Sunday evenings, 7:00-9:00 p.m. September 21; October 5 &amp;
            19; November 2, 16 &amp; 30</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>
        Specific Officer Training
    </h3>
    <ul type="disc">
        <li>Self-study will focus on biblical qualifications and character and practical training
            for the role of ruling elder or deacon through study, mentoring and activities in
            keeping with PCA <i>Book of Church Order</i> requirements.</li>
        <li>Meeting schedule: Sunday evenings, 7:00-9:00 p.m.
        <ul type="disc">
            <li>Ruling Elder: January 4 &amp; 18, February 1 &amp; 15</li>
            <li>Deacon: January 11 &amp; 25; February 8 &amp; 22</li>
        </ul></li>
    </ul>
        <p>
            Ordination to office would be contingent on examination and an interview with the
            Session and election by the congregation.
            <br />
        </p>
